def return_missing_values(df):
    print("Percentage of missing values")
    print("============================")

    for var in df.columns:
        if df[var].isna().sum() >0:
            miss = np.round(df[var].isna().sum()/df.shape[0] * 100,3)
            print(var, "has {0}% of missing values".format(miss))

def clean_Text(text,flag):
    
    #Make text lowercase
    text = text.lower()
    
    #remove text in square brackets
    text = re.sub('\[.*?\]', '', text)
    
    #remove links
    text = re.sub('https?://\S+|www\.\S+', '', text)
    
    #remove html
    text = re.sub('<.*?>+', '', text)
    
    #remove punctuation except hashtag mark
    x=punctuation
    y=""
    if flag:
        y=x[0:2]+x[3:13]+x[14:]
    else:
        y=x[0:2]+x[3:] 
    text = re.sub('[%s]' % re.escape(y), '', text)
    
    #remove \n
    text = re.sub('\n', '', text)
    
    #remove Emoji
    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
                           u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  # emoticons
                           u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"  # symbols & pictographs
                           u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  # transport & map symbols
                           u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  # flags (iOS)
                           u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
                           u"\U000024C2-\U0001F251"
                           "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
        
    
    return emoji_pattern.sub(r'', text)

def remove_Stopword_Lemmatize_Msg(msg):
    
    # converting messages to lowercase
    msg = msg.lower()
    
    # removing stopwords
    msg = [word for word in msg.split() if word not in stopwords]

    # using a stemmer
    #stemmer = stem.PorterStemmer()
    #msg = " ".join([stemmer.stem(word) for word in msg])
    
    # using a Lemmatizer
    # lemmatization is preferred over Stemming because lemmatization does morphological analysis of the words.
    wnl = nltk.WordNetLemmatizer()
    msg =" ".join([wnl.lemmatize(word) for word in msg])
    
    return msg

def get_Hashtags(text):
    l=re.findall("#\w+",text)
    rl=[]
    for i in l:
        rl.append(i[1:])
    return " ".join(rl)

def unusual_words(text):
    text_vocab = set(w.lower() for w in text if w.isalpha())
    english_vocab = set(w.lower() for w in nltk.corpus.words.words())
    unusual = text_vocab - english_vocab
    return sorted(unusual)

def build_wordcloud(df, title):
    wordcloud = WordCloud(
        background_color='gray', 
        stopwords=set(STOPWORDS), 
        max_words=50, 
        max_font_size=40, 
        random_state=666
    ).generate(str(df))

    fig = plt.figure(1, figsize=(14,14))
    plt.axis('off')
    fig.suptitle(title, fontsize=16)
    fig.subplots_adjust(top=2.3)

    plt.imshow(wordcloud)
    plt.show()

def generate_sent(model, num_words, random_seed=42):
    """
    :param model: An ngram language model from `nltk.lm.model`.
    :param num_words: Max no. of words to generate.
    :param random_seed: Seed value for random.
    """
    content = []
    for token in model.generate(num_words, random_seed=random_seed):
        if token == '<s>':
            continue
        if token == '</s>':
            break
        content.append(token)
    return detokenize(content)

def plot_history(history):
    acc = history.history['accuracy']
    val_acc = history.history['val_accuracy']
    loss = history.history['loss']
    val_loss = history.history['val_loss']
    x = range(1, len(acc) + 1)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(x, acc, 'b', label='Training acc')
    plt.plot(x, val_acc, 'r', label='Validation acc')
    plt.title('Training and validation accuracy')
    plt.legend()
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(x, loss, 'b', label='Training loss')
    plt.plot(x, val_loss, 'r', label='Validation loss')
    plt.title('Training and validation loss')
    plt.legend()

Clustering¶

clusteringis the task of dividing the population or data points into a number of groups such that data points in the same groups are more similar to other data points in the same group than those in other groups. In simple words, the aim is to segregate groups with similar traits and assign them into clusters.¶

We use Kmeans clustering algotithm to split data into 2 clusters.¶

How does K-Means clustering algorithm work? Explained in 6 Points.¶

1. K points randomly selected as cluster centers(centroids).¶

2. All the nearest points to these K centroids form a cluster.¶

3. Means of all points of various clusters is found.¶

4. These mean points are the new cluster centers or centroids.¶

5. Repeat steps 2 to 4 until the centroids stop moving or changing or stopping criteria is reached like maximum iterations etc.¶

6. Final centroids are cluster centers and all the points nearest to a centroid belong to that cluster.¶

We use Tfidf Vectorizer to get the features¶

def clean_Text_1(text,flag=""):
    
    #Make text lowercase
    text = text.lower()
    
    #remove text in square brackets
    text = re.sub('\[.*?\]', '', text)
    
    #remove links
    text = re.sub('https?://\S+|www\.\S+', '', text)
    
    #remove html
    text = re.sub('<.*?>+', '', text)
    
    #remove the hashtags
    if flag == "removeHashtags" :
      text = re.sub('#\w*[a-zA-Z]\w*','',text)
    
    #split Hashtags
    if flag == "splitHashtags":
      text = re.sub('[_#]', ' ', text)

    #remove punctuation
    x=punctuation
    y=x[0:2]+x[3:26]+x[27:]
    text = re.sub('[%s]' % re.escape(y), '', text)

    #remove \n
    text = re.sub('\n', '', text)
    
    text = text.strip()

    #Keep these characters
    text = re.sub("[^A-Za-z0-9#@+_ ]","",text) 

    #remove Emoji
    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
                           u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  # emoticons
                           u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"  # symbols & pictographs
                           u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  # transport & map symbols
                           u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  # flags (iOS)
                           u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
                           u"\U000024C2-\U0001F251"
                           "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
        
    
    return emoji_pattern.sub(r'', text)

def cvt5CTo2C(x):
    if x == 'Extremely Negative' or x == 'Negative' :
        return 0
    if x == 'Positive' or x == 'Extremely Positive' :
        return 1
    return 2

def cvt5CToNumerical5C(x):
    if x == 'Extremely Negative' :
        return 0
    if x == 'Negative' : 
        return 1
    if x == 'Positive' :
        return 2
    if x == 'Extremely Positive' : 
        return 3
    return 4

def train_evaluate_model(Model_Name, Model, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
    print(f'Start. {Model_Name.upper()}......')
    Model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = Model.predict(X_test)
    y_train_pred = Model.predict(X_train)
    print(f'Accuracy On Testing Data --> {Model_Name.upper()}: \t\t{accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred) * 100:.2f}%')
    print(f'Accuracy On Training Data --> {Model_Name.upper()}: \t\t{accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred) * 100:.2f}%')
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))
    print(f'End. {Model_Name.upper()}')
    print('======================================================')
    return y_pred

def plot_history(history):
    acc = history.history['accuracy']
    val_acc = history.history['val_accuracy']
    loss = history.history['loss']
    val_loss = history.history['val_loss']
    x = range(1, len(acc) + 1)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(x, acc, 'b', label='Training acc')
    plt.plot(x, val_acc, 'r', label='Validation acc')
    plt.title('Training and validation accuracy')
    plt.legend()
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(x, loss, 'b', label='Training loss')
    plt.plot(x, val_loss, 'r', label='Validation loss')
    plt.title('Training and validation loss')
    plt.legend()

def plot_loss_evaluation(r):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

    plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(r.history['loss'], label='loss')
    plt.plot(r.history['val_loss'], label='val_loss')
    plt.legend()

    plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(r.history['accuracy'], label='accuracy')
    plt.plot(r.history['val_accuracy'], label='val_acc')
    plt.legend()

def evaluate(model, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
  
    y_pred_train = np.round(model.predict(X_train))
    y_pred_test = np.round(model.predict(X_test))
    
    print("=============Training Data===============")
    print(confusion_matrix(y_train, y_pred_train))
    print(classification_report(y_train, y_pred_train))
    print(f"Accuracy score: {accuracy_score(y_train, y_pred_train) * 100:.2f}%")
    
    print("=============Testing Data===============")
    print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test))
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_test))
    print(f"Accuracy score: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_test) * 100:.2f}%")

def ML_Classifiers_using_bag_of_word(train_x,train_y,test_x,test_y):
  vectorizer = CountVectorizer()
  vectorizer.fit(train_x)
  X_train = vectorizer.transform(train_x)
  X_test  = vectorizer.transform(test_x)
  print(f'X_train shape: {X_train.shape}, train_y shape: {train_y.shape}')
  print(f'X_test shape: {X_test.shape}, test_y shape: {test_y.shape}')

  LR_model_1 = LogisticRegression()
  NB_model_1 = MultinomialNB()
  SVM_model_1 = LinearSVC()
  LR_y_pred_using_bag_of_word = train_evaluate_model('Logistic Regression', LR_model_1, X_train, X_test, train_y, test_y)
  nb_y_pred_using_bag_of_word = train_evaluate_model('Naive Bayes', NB_model_1, X_train, X_test, train_y, test_y)

def ML_Classifiers_using_tf_idf(train_x,train_y,test_x,test_y):
  vectorizer1 = TfidfVectorizer(max_df=0.5,min_df=2)
  X_train_vect = vectorizer1.fit_transform(train_x)
  X_test_vect  = vectorizer1.transform(test_x)
  print(f'X_train shape: {X_train_vect.shape}, train_y shape: {train_y.shape}')
  print(f'X_test shape: {X_test_vect.shape}, test_y shape: {test_y.shape}')
  LR_model_2 = LogisticRegression()
  NB_model_2 = MultinomialNB()
  SVM_model_2 = LinearSVC()
  LR_y_pred_using_using_tf_idf = train_evaluate_model('Logistic Regression', LR_model_2, X_train_vect, X_test_vect, train_y, test_y)
  nb_y_pred_pred_using_tf_idf = train_evaluate_model('Naive Bayes', NB_model_2, X_train_vect, X_test_vect, train_y, test_y)
  svm_y_pred_using_tf_idf = train_evaluate_model('Support Vector Machine', SVM_model_2, X_train_vect, X_test_vect, train_y, test_y)

  • Bidirectional LSTM layer
  • Bidirectional LSTM layer
  • Dropout layer

def cvtTexts2Sequences(train_x,test_x): 
  MAX_VOCAB_SIZE = 5000
  tokenizer = Tokenizer(num_words=MAX_VOCAB_SIZE) 
  tokenizer.fit_on_texts(train_x)
  sequences_train = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(train_x)
  sequences_test = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(test_x)
  data_train = pad_sequences(sequences_train , padding='post')
  data_test = pad_sequences(sequences_test, padding='post' , maxlen=data_train.shape[1])
  print(f"Found {len(tokenizer.word_index)} unique tokens.")
  print(f"Training Data shape: {data_train.shape}")
  print(f"Testing Data shape: {data_test.shape}")
  return data_train , data_test , len(tokenizer.word_index) + 1

def DeepLearingModelOnPostiveAndNegativeClasses(data_train,data_test,train_y,test_y,Max_Vocab_Size):
  #tf.keras.backend.clear_session()
  embedding_dim = 100
  units = 128
  EPOCHS = 10 
  BATCH_SIZE = 32 
  MAX_VOCAB_SIZE = Max_Vocab_Size
  model = Sequential() 
  model.add(layers.Embedding(MAX_VOCAB_SIZE, embedding_dim, input_length=data_train.shape[1] )) 
  model.add(Bidirectional( LSTM(units,return_sequences=True) ) ) 
  model.add(Bidirectional ( LSTM(units) ) ) 
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
  opt = tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(learning_rate=0.0008)
  my_callbacks = [
      tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(patience=3,restore_best_weights=True),
      tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor="val_loss",factor=0.1,patience=10,verbose=0,mode="auto",min_delta=0.0001,cooldown=0, min_lr=0)
  ]
  model.compile(optimizer=opt ,loss='binary_crossentropy',metrics=['accuracy'])
  model.summary()
  history = model.fit(data_train, train_y, epochs=EPOCHS, validation_data=(data_test, test_y), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE , callbacks=my_callbacks)
  loss_1, accuracy_1 = model.evaluate(data_train, train_y, verbose=False)
  print("Training Accuracy: {:.4f}".format(accuracy_1))
  print("Training Loss: {:.4f}".format(loss_1))
  loss_2, accuracy_2 = model.evaluate(data_test, test_y, verbose=False)
  print("Testing Accuracy: {:.4f}".format(accuracy_2))
  print("Testing Loss:  {:.4f}".format(loss_2))
  plot_history(history)
  return model

def DeepLearingModelFor5Classes(data_train,data_test,train_y,test_y,Max_Vocab_Size):
  embedding_dim = 100
  units = 128 
  EPOCHS = 10 
  BATCH_SIZE = 32 
  MAX_VOCAB_SIZE = Max_Vocab_Size
  model = Sequential() 
  model.add(layers.Embedding(MAX_VOCAB_SIZE, embedding_dim, input_length=data_train.shape[1] )) 
  model.add( Bidirectional( LSTM(units,return_sequences=True) ) ) 
  model.add( Bidirectional( LSTM(units) ) )
  model.add(Dropout(0.2))
  model.add(layers.Dense(5, activation='softmax'))

  opt = tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(learning_rate=0.0008)
  my_callbacks = [
      tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(patience=3,restore_best_weights=True),
      tf.keras.callbacks.ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor="val_loss",factor=0.1,patience=10,verbose=0,mode="auto",min_delta=0.0001,cooldown=0, min_lr=0)
  ]
  model.compile(optimizer=opt ,loss=SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True),metrics=['accuracy'])
  model.summary()

  history = model.fit(data_train, train_y, epochs=EPOCHS, validation_data=(data_test, test_y), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE , callbacks=my_callbacks )

  loss_1, accuracy_1 = model.evaluate(data_train, train_y, verbose=False)
  print("Training Accuracy: {:.4f}".format(accuracy_1))
  print("Training Loss: {:.4f}".format(loss_1))
  loss_2, accuracy_2 = model.evaluate(data_test, test_y, verbose=False)
  print("Testing Accuracy: {:.4f}".format(accuracy_2))
  print("Testing Loss:  {:.4f}".format(loss_2))
  plot_history(history)
  return model

def testing_result(path):
    global df,df_binary_sentiment
    model2_tweets_without_hashtags = load_model("Model2_tweets_without_hashtags.h5")
    model5_tweets_without_hashtags = load_model("Model5_tweets_without_hashtags.h5")
    df1 = pd.read_csv(path,encoding="latin1")
    df1['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'] = df1['OriginalTweet'].apply(lambda x: clean_Text_1(x,"removeHashtags"))
    df1['Sentiment2'] = df1['Sentiment'].apply(lambda x: cvt5CTo2C(x))
    df1['Sentiment5'] = df1['Sentiment'].apply(lambda x: cvt5CToNumerical5C(x))
    df_binary_sentiment1 = df1[ df1['Sentiment2'] != 2 ]
    
    MAX_VOCAB_SIZE = 5000
    
    tokenizer = Tokenizer(num_words=MAX_VOCAB_SIZE) 
    tokenizer.fit_on_texts(df_binary_sentiment['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'])
    sequences_train = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(df_binary_sentiment['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'])
    sequences_test = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(df_binary_sentiment1['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'])
    data_train = pad_sequences(sequences_train , padding='post')
    data_test = pad_sequences(sequences_test, padding='post' , maxlen=data_train.shape[1])

    loss2, accuracy2 = model2_tweets_without_hashtags.evaluate(data_test, df_binary_sentiment1['Sentiment2'] , verbose=False)
    print("Binary classification using Deep Neural Networks-- > Testing Accuracy : {:.4f}".format(accuracy2))
    
    print("\nML_Classifiers_using_bag_of_word on 2 classes")
    ML_Classifiers_using_bag_of_word(df_binary_sentiment['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'], df_binary_sentiment['Sentiment2'] ,df_binary_sentiment1['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'], df_binary_sentiment1['Sentiment2'] )
    print("\nML_Classifiers_using_tf_idf on 2 classes")
    ML_Classifiers_using_tf_idf(df_binary_sentiment['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'], df_binary_sentiment['Sentiment2'] ,df_binary_sentiment1['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'], df_binary_sentiment1['Sentiment2'] )
    
    tokenizer1 = Tokenizer(num_words=MAX_VOCAB_SIZE) 
    tokenizer1.fit_on_texts(df['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'])
    sequences_train = tokenizer1.texts_to_sequences(df['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'])
    sequences_test = tokenizer1.texts_to_sequences(df1['OriginalTweet_without_hashtags'])
    data_train = pad_sequences(sequences_train , padding='post')
    data_test = pad_sequences(sequences_test, padding='post' , maxlen=data_train.shape[1])
    
    loss5, accuracy5 = model5_tweets_without_hashtags.evaluate(data_test, df['Sentiment5'] , verbose=False)
    print("Multiclass classification using Deep Neural Networks -- > Testing Accuracy : {:.4f}".format(accuracy5))
